info.author: Michael B. Trausch
info.description:
This package provides for a (hopefully) clean, simple wrapper around
mcrypt that can be used from both Python 2 and Python 3 code.  It is
presently not yet stable, and it can be expected that the interface
will not be stable until at least a few versions from now; it will
definitely be stable by 1.0, but it is hoped way before then.
info.name: pymcrypt
